This paper deals with wireless communication networks and optimization of throughput. The paper discusses the use of wireless energy transfer to power the communication devices, which falls under the category of wireless power transfer. The optimization problem involves time allocation for both energy transfer and information transmission, which is a typical problem in information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the coordination of wireless energy/information transmissions, which is a topic in networked systems, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of convex optimization techniques, which is a common tool in control systems and optimization, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. The paper also discusses simulation results, which may fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
